NORTHWEST
•Airmanship
Airmanship ... The knowledge and skill
in all things pertaining to the operation,
maintenance, management and safety of air
transportation and the achievement of the
highest standards of public service.
When you and your family
fly Northwest Orient Airlines,
you get with your ticket a priceless
quality of assurance called Airmanship ... won
in more than a third of a century of flying over
land and sea. Northwest superior Airmanship
is the total skill of many people-in the air and
on the ground —working toward a common
goal: your safety, satisfaction and peace of mind.
Northwest Airmanship is modern air travel
efficiency at its best. Today, as always, superior
Airmanship is the watchword for every one
of our more than 7,000 Northwest employees.
Donald V. Nyo
PRESIDENT
NORTHWEST Orient AIRLINES
2009.083.003
Meet the fleet... now
headed by the monarch
of the Big Jets...
NORTHWEST'S IMPERIAL DC-8C
In its 34 years of expanding operations, Northwest
Orient Airlines has flown most of the great aircraft
ever built. Out of that long and broad experience
comes the belief that the present Northwest air-
fleet is the finest that money can buy.
During 1960, the magnificent Douglas DC-8C be-
comes the leader of the fleet.
The immense
swept-back
wings of the DC-8C
measure 142' 4" from tip to tip. Fully loaded, these
wings contain 23,307 gallons of jet fuel. Filling these
wing tanks is equivalent to filling about 900 auto-
mobile tanks all at one time; yet we do this big
job in 15 to 20 minutes.
Designed for cruising at speeds close to 600 miles
per hour, the DC-8C is about the most "automatic"
airliner yet devised. It has eighteen separate elec-
tronic systems. These handle such diverse needs as
radar weather spotting and air conditioning built
to meet outside temperatures from 100 above zero
to 100 below.
In comfort and
roominess, the Imperial DC-8C
ushers in a new era for the air traveler. Each seat
has its own reading light,
cold
air outlet,
call
button, aisle light,
ashtray,
table and individual
oxygen equipment. Hi-fi speakers carry music and
announcements throughout the cabin.
Pressuriza-
tion is so highly developed that at 23,000 feet the
cabin
pressure is
exactly equal to atmospheric
pressure at sea-level.
More than just a new airliner, this Big Jet is truly
a new way of life for the traveler. We invite you
to enjoy it to the fullest.
